Requirements:  
1. PHP 5.2.0 and higher
2. MySQL database 4.1.1 and higher
3. Web server (Apache, IIS, etc.)

1. Download a latest version of platform.

2. Extract archive to directory when you want to install the platform.

3. Create virtual host:

  <VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName somedomain

    DocumentRoot "/path/to/htdocs"

    ErrorLog "/path/to/log/error.log"
    CustomLog "/path/to/log/access.log" combined

    php_value error_log "/path/to/log/php.log"

    RewriteEngine on
    RewriteMap lowercase int:tolower

    <Directory "/path/to/htdocs">
      Options Includes FollowSymLinks Indexes
      AllowOverride all
      Order allow,deny
      Allow from all
    </Directory>

  </VirtualHost>

3. Change permission for cache dirsctory to world-writeable (chmod 777).

4. Go to http://somedomain/install/ via web browser and following instructions.